As the US continues to disregard the international rules that have helped govern the global financial and trade order for decades and imposes sanctions on any country that does not bend to its political will, a revolt is slowly but surely shaping up against Washington's financial hegemony. How thunderous is the call to challenge the US dollar's hegemony? (See story on Page S4-5 )  
